Overview

The world ocean is 362,033,000 km2 (Menard & Smith, 1966 in Jakobsson et al., 2002). According to Jakobsson et al.(2002) the Arctic Ocean, as defined by the International Hydrographic Organization (1953), is 15,551,000 km2 or about 4.3% of the global ocean.

In the present analysis, the Arctic Ocean is as defined by the International Hydrographic Organization (1953) using the following dataset:

International Hydrographic Organization, IHO; Sieger, Rainer (2012): Limits of oceans and seas in digitized, machine readable form. Alfred Wegener Institute, Helmholtz Centre for Polar and Marine Research, Bremerhaven, PANGAEA, https://doi.org/10.1594/PANGAEA.777975

Calculation of the surface area of the Arctic Ocean using GMT (script below) was finally not used:

  • north of 60N: 1.6751e+07 km2, or 4.6% of the global ocean.
  • north of 75N: 7.11213e+06 km2, or 2% of the global ocean.

Comparison

With the Arctic region investigated for both products we now want to compare them for the Arctic, Atlantic, Indian, Pacific, and Southern oceans. For both the full oceans as well as coastal (<= 200 m bottom depth) values. To do so we will use the bottom depths accompanied by the products.

Appendix: GMT script

Works but results not used in the manuscript in the end.


bash
cd
cd "pCloud Drive/FACE-IT_data/maps/GEBCO/"

# masque terre
gmt grdlandmask -Gnewmask.nc -RGEBCO_2020.nc -Df -N1/NaN/NaN/NaN/NaN

# selection de l ocean a partir du masques
gmt grdmath GEBCO_2020.nc newmask.nc OR = wet0.nc
# il reste des valeurs positives que j'limine
gmt grdclip wet0.nc -Gwet.nc -Sa0/NaN

# calcul de la surface de l ocean, latitude > 75 degrs
#  la valeur -10000 que j'ai donne  l'option -C de grdvolume
#  est une profondeur (en valeur absolue suprieure  la profondeur maximale
#  de l'ocan), ce qui permet, si j'ai bien compris le fonctionnement
#  de grdvolume) de prendre en compte toute la surface de l'ocan
gmt grdvolume wet.nc -R-180/180/75/90 -C-10000 -Sk > grdv_wet_75

# calcul de la surface de l ocean, latitude > 60 degrs
gmt grdvolume wet.nc -R-180/180/60/90 -C-10000 -Sk > grdv_wet_60.txt

# la surface est la somme des surfaces des 2 demi-hmisphres
#   (la surface est la 2ime valeur sortie par grdvolume)
#   (l unit de surface est le km2)
cat grdv_wet_75_dh? | awk 'BEGIN{s=0};{s=s+$2};END{print s}'
# 7.11213e+06
# Moi je trouve 7112242
cat grdv_wet_60_dh? | awk 'BEGIN{s=0};{s=s+$2};END{print s}'
# 1.6751e+07
# Moi je trouve 16768436

# j ai calcul pour latitude > 60 afin de comparer avec la surface
#  de l ocan arctique donne par wikipdia : 1.4e+7 km2
